---
import Layout from '../../../layouts/Layout.astro';

const products = [
  {
    name: 'Diffusion Plate Cleaning and Inspection Production Line',
    image: '/assets/img/automation/product-a.jpg',
    href: '/products/automation/product-a',
    desc: 'Integrated production line for diffusion plate cleaning, inspection, and continuous conveying with stable industrial workflow.'
  },
  {
    name: 'Robotic Automatic Loading and Unloading Cleaning Machine',
    image: '/assets/img/automation/product-b.jpg',
    href: '/products/automation/product-b',
    desc: 'Automated cleaning equipment with mechanical loading and unloading support for improved efficiency and reduced manual handling.'
  },
  {
    name: 'Polarizer Absorption Axis Angle Measuring System',
    image: '/assets/img/automation/product-c.jpg',
    href: '/products/automation/product-c',
    desc: 'High-precision measuring system for polarizer absorption axis angle, retardation, chromaticity, and transmittance analysis.'
  }
];
---

<Layout title="Industrial Automation Equipment | Display Manufacturing Lines | DGSDK"
  description="DGSDK industrial automation equipment: diffusion plate cleaning lines, robotic loading/unloading systems, and polarizer measurement instruments for display manufacturing.">
  <section
    class="products-hero"
    style="background: linear-gradient(rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.28), rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.18)), url('/assets/img/automation/automation-bg.png') center/cover no-repeat;"
  >
    <div class="container products-hero-inner">
      <span class="products-hero-kicker">DGSDK Product Portfolio</span>
      <h1>Automation Equipment</h1>
      <p>
        Efficient industrial automation solutions designed to improve production
        consistency, reduce labor costs, and support customized manufacturing needs.
      </p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="products-overview-section">
    <div class="container products-overview-layout">
      <aside class="products-sidebar">
        <div class="products-sidebar-box">
          <h3>Browse Categories</h3>
          <a href="/products">All Products</a>
          <a href="/products/static-eliminator">Static Elimination Systems</a>
          <a href="/products/cleaning-machine">Cleaning Machine</a>
          <a href="/products/precision-machined-parts">Precision Machined Parts</a>
          <a href="/products/automation" class="active-category">Automation Equipment</a>
        </div>
      </aside>

      <div class="products-main">
        <section class="apple-product-section">
          <div class="apple-card-grid">
            {products.map((product) => (
              <a href={product.href} class="apple-product-card">
                <img src={product.image} alt={product.name} loading="lazy" />

                <div class="apple-product-card-body">
                  <span class="apple-card-tag">Automation Equipment</span>
                  <h3>{product.name}</h3>
                  <p>{product.desc}</p>
                </div>
              </a>
            ))}
          </div>
        </section>

        <section class="category-info-block">
          <h2>About DGSDK Automation Equipment</h2>
          <p>DGSDK designs and manufactures industrial automation equipment for electronics manufacturing, optical film processing, and display component production. Our automation systems integrate mechanical handling, precision cleaning, automated inspection, and measurement into one production line. This reduces manual labor and improves output consistency.</p>
          <p>We develop each automation system around the customer's requirements. These include throughput targets, material types, and integration with existing line equipment. Custom configurations are available for specialized applications.</p>

          <h3>Diffusion Plate Cleaning and Inspection Production Line</h3>
          <p>The <a href="/products/automation/product-a">diffusion plate cleaning and inspection production line</a> is an integrated system for LED and LCD display manufacturing. It combines surface cleaning, optical inspection, and continuous conveying into a single automated process. The integrated design eliminates manual intervention between process steps. This reduces particle risk and improves throughput consistency.</p>
          <p>Display component manufacturers use this system when they need stable, repeatable cleaning and inspection results across high-volume production runs.</p>

          <h3>Robotic Loading and Unloading Cleaning Machine</h3>
          <p>The <a href="/products/automation/product-b">robotic automatic loading and unloading cleaning machine</a> uses a mechanical arm to move substrates in and out of the cleaning station. This removes the need for manual intervention at the transfer point. Labor costs drop. The system cuts handling-related defects. It fits different substrate sizes and production speeds.</p>

          <h3>Polarizer Absorption Axis Angle Measuring System</h3>
          <p>The <a href="/products/automation/product-c">polarizer absorption axis angle measuring instrument</a> provides high-precision measurement of polarizer optical properties. It measures absorption axis angle, retardation value, chromaticity, and transmittance. Engineers use these measurements for incoming quality control and in-process checks during polarizer manufacturing and lamination.</p>

          <h3>Automation Equipment Applications</h3>
          <ul>
            <li>Diffusion plate cleaning and optical inspection production lines for display manufacturing</li>
            <li>Robotic loading and unloading cleaning systems for high-volume flat panel production</li>
            <li>Polarizer absorption axis angle measurement for quality control in polarizer processing</li>
            <li>Custom automation integration for electronics assembly and optical component manufacturing</li>
          </ul>
          <p>Contact us to discuss your automation requirements and receive a customized system proposal.</p>

          <h3>Industrial Automation for Display Manufacturing</h3>
          <p>Display component manufacturing has specific automation challenges. Substrates such as diffusion plates, polarizer films, and backlight panels are large and fragile. They are highly sensitive to surface particles. Manual handling introduces scratches and static-related defects at every transfer point.</p>
          <p>Automated handling systems move substrates through cleaning, inspection, and packaging stages without direct human contact. This approach removes these risks.</p>
          <p>DGSDK's automation equipment meets strict cleanliness standards for display manufacturing. Conveyor speeds, handling pressures, and inspection parameters are all configurable. We use custom mechanical and electrical connections to link each machine to your existing line.</p>

          <h3>Custom Automation System Integration</h3>
          <p>Standard automation equipment covers the most common production configurations. Many electronics and display manufacturing lines need customized solutions. DGSDK develops custom automation systems based on detailed customer requirements. These include substrate type and dimensions, throughput target, cleanroom classification, and integration points with upstream and downstream equipment.</p>
          <p>Custom projects begin with a technical review of the production requirements. We provide a system design proposal covering the mechanical layout, process flow, and control architecture. We give estimated lead time before any commitment. System integrators work directly with production teams. They validate designs against real world production conditions before commissioning.</p>
          <p>This ensures the delivered system meets the production line's requirements from day one. Our customer service team supports each project from initial review through final acceptance testing. Contact us to begin a technical review for your automation project.</p>

          <h3>Benefits of Automation Integration for Manufacturing</h3>
          <p>Automation enables consistent output, lower labor costs, and better quality control. Each cycle repeats the same motion, force, and timing. This reduces defects from operator variation. Automation also streamlines business processes by linking production data across stations.</p>
          <p>Integrated solutions combine multiple process steps into one continuous line. Cleaning, inspection, and handling occur without manual transfer. This saves time and reduces labor costs at every stage.</p>
          <p>Automation reduces costs over time. Labor requirements decrease. Automated inspection catches defects early and reduces scrap rates. Quality assurance becomes part of the production process rather than a separate step.</p>
          <p>Real-time data from automated inspection systems gives production teams immediate feedback. Teams spot problems as they occur. Operators adjust process parameters without waiting for end-of-line sampling.</p>
          <p>DGSDK acts as a system integrator for customers who need a complete production line. We design the mechanical layout, specify each process station, write the control software, and commission the system on-site. This single-source approach simplifies project management and accountability.</p>
          <p>Display manufacturing automation tools must meet strict cleanliness standards. All mechanical components that contact substrates are designed for low particle generation. Control systems log process data at each station and share data with process management systems.</p>
          <p>Inspection algorithms can incorporate machine learning and artificial intelligence ai to improve defect detection over time. This supports data integrity and traceability for quality assurance reporting. Contact us to discuss how automation integration can improve your production line efficiency and output quality.</p>

          <h3>Working with an Automation System Integrator</h3>
          <p>A system integrator manages the full scope of an automation project. This covers design, supply, build, and start-up. One team handles the whole job. This cuts down on hand-off errors and project delays.</p>
          <p>DGSDK acts as your automation system integrator from start to finish. We review your process and design the system. We build the equipment and test it on-site. Our customer service team stays involved after delivery to support your operators.</p>
          <p>Working with a single integrator reduces risk. You deal with one point of contact. All parts of the system are designed to work together from day one. Start-up is faster and smoother as a result.</p>
          <p>Our team handles all aspects of the project. We manage the timeline and keep you informed at each stage. This lets your team focus on running production while we handle the build and commissioning.</p>

          <h3>Automation Equipment and Quality Control</h3>
          <p>Automated systems improve quality control at every step. Each machine in the line runs the same check the same way. There is no change from one shift to the next. This gives you a stable, consistent output every day.</p>
          <p>DGSDK automation systems log data at each process point. You can track output rates, check counts, and alarm events in real time. This makes it easy to find the root cause of any quality issue fast.</p>
          <p>Consistent data helps with customer reports and audit records. You can show that each production run met the required standards. This supports quality assurance and builds trust with your customers.</p>
          <p>Good data also helps you plan maintenance. You can see when a machine is starting to drift from its normal range. You can act before a defect reaches the customer. This reduces waste and keeps your production line running well.</p>
        </section>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>
</Layout>